Harvard Names Alan Garber of Stanford as Its Next Provost

-- B y   J o h n   L a u e r m a n
-- 
2011-04-15T18:49:51Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-15/harvard-names-alan-garber-of-stanford-as-its-next-provost.html
Harvard University  named Alan Garber, a Stanford University professor of medicine and
economics, as its next provost, replacing Steven Hyman, who will
step down at the end of the academic year.  Harvard, based in Cambridge,  Massachusetts , released the
information in a  statement  on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
John Lauerman in  Boston  at 
 jlauerman@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jonathan Kaufman at 
 jkaufman17@bloomberg.net . 